### 1.1b â€” AI Provider Abstraction Layer (Plug & Play)

> [!TIP]
> **Design goal:** Swap LLM or embedding provider by changing **only [.env](file:///d:/Projects/MERN/Vaanix/.env) variables** â€” zero code changes. Add a new provider by implementing a single interface file.

Create a new shared package `packages/ai-providers` with a registry-based architecture.

#### [NEW] `packages/ai-providers/package.json`
- New workspace package `@vaanix/ai-providers`
- Dependencies: `openai`, `@google/generative-ai`, `@azure/openai` (as optional peers)

#### [NEW] `packages/ai-providers/src/index.ts`
- Re-exports all public interfaces, the registry, and helper functions

#### [NEW] `packages/ai-providers/src/types.ts`
- Unified interfaces:

```typescript
// --- LLM Provider ---
interface LLMProvider {
  id: string;                       // 'openai' | 'azure' | 'google' | ...
  chat(params: ChatParams): Promise<ChatResponse>;
  chatStream(params: ChatParams): AsyncIterable<ChatChunk>;
}

interface ChatParams {
  model: string;
  messages: ChatMessage[];
  temperature?: number;
  maxTokens?: number;
}

// --- Embedding Provider ---
interface EmbeddingProvider {
  id: string;                       // 'openai' | 'cohere' | ...
  embed(texts: string[]): Promise<number[][]>;
  dimensions: number;
}
```

#### [NEW] `packages/ai-providers/src/registry.ts`
- **Provider registry** with auto-discovery from [.env](file:///d:/Projects/MERN/Vaanix/.env):

```typescript
// Reads LLM_PROVIDER and EMBEDDING_PROVIDER from env
// Maps to the correct implementation automatically
export function getLLMProvider(overrideId?: string): LLMProvider;
export function getEmbeddingProvider(overrideId?: string): EmbeddingProvider;
export function listAvailableProviders(): { llm: string[]; embedding: string[] };
```

#### [NEW] `packages/ai-providers/src/providers/openai.ts`
- OpenAI implementation of `LLMProvider` + `EmbeddingProvider`
- Reads `OPENAI_API_KEY` from env
- Supports: gpt-4o, gpt-4o-mini, text-embedding-3-small, text-embedding-3-large

#### [NEW] `packages/ai-providers/src/providers/google.ts`
- Google Gemini implementation of `LLMProvider`
- Reads `GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY` from env
- Supports: gemini-2.0-flash, gemini-1.5-pro

#### [NEW] `packages/ai-providers/src/providers/azure.ts`
- Azure OpenAI implementation of `LLMProvider` + `EmbeddingProvider`
- Reads `AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY`, `AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT` from env

#### [.env](file:///d:/Projects/MERN/Vaanix/.env) additions:
```env
# --- AI Providers (plug & play) ---
LLM_PROVIDER="openai"              # openai | google | azure
LLM_MODEL="gpt-4o-mini"
EMBEDDING_PROVIDER="openai"        # openai | azure
EMBEDDING_MODEL="text-embedding-3-small"

OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
# GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY="..."          # uncomment to enable
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY="..."       # uncomment to enable
# AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT="..."
```

#### How it works at runtime:
1. Agent has `modelProvider` and `modelId` stored in DB â€” this is the **per-agent override**
2. If agent has no override, falls back to `LLM_PROVIDER` / `LLM_MODEL` from [.env](file:///d:/Projects/MERN/Vaanix/.env)
3. `getLLMProvider('openai')` returns the OpenAI implementation, `getLLMProvider('google')` returns Gemini, etc.
4. Adding a new provider = create one file implementing `LLMProvider`, register it in the registry â€” done

